Reasoning: The paper deals with the interpretation of the attack relation in argumentation using strong negation in classical logic. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for its applications in reasoning and decision-making, logic (cs.LO) for its use of classical logic, computational linguistics (cs.CL) for its relevance to natural language argumentation, cryptography (cs.CR) for its use of logic in security protocols, and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) for its relevance to the representation and manipulation of argumentation networks.
